user.canProvide: Come to me with any and all event ideas, feedback, dream Retreat locations, and sponsorship requests. I'm also passionate about supporting women in tech and excited to continue to build more opportunities for the incredible women in our community.
user.currentRole: VP of Events and Experiences @ Contrary

educationExperiences.degreeType: Graduated Magma Cum Laude with a Bachelor of Arts (B.A.) degree

user.intro:
I'm Jess Contrary's Director of Events leading our efforts for all things events marketing across our Fellowship, Venture Partners, Portfolio, and beyond. 

A little more about me: Originally born in the Bay Area, I grew up in CT before attending Northeastern University in Boston. I've moved around a bit since college (Denver -> Boston -> Oakland), and found my way back to Denver last October because of my love for everything outdoors.
user.lookingFor: Always looking to learn more about Web3, climate tech, the future of work/HR tech, and creative community-building tactics and events.
user.meetWithBlurb: Let's chat about all of your event ideas and feedback, how to get more involved in your local hub or as a VP, women in tech, and really anything else!
